meanings.definition: "discriminato" is not a standard English word. It seems to be a misspelling or an Italian word. If you meant "discriminated", see the entry for "discriminate". If you meant the Italian word, it is the past participle of the verb "discriminare" (to discriminate).
meanings.english_definition: "discriminato" is not a standard English word. It may be a misspelling or an Italian word. If you meant "discriminated", see the entry for "discriminate". If you meant the Italian word, it is the past participle of the verb "discriminare" (to discriminate).

usage_notes.explanation: The word "discriminato" does not exist in standard English. If you are looking for information on the English word, please check the spelling or search for "discriminate". If you are referring to the Italian word, it is the past participle of the verb "discriminare".
